$ Data mining: steps

A commonly agreed upon model for data mining follows these steps:
   • Understand the business problem.
   • Understand the data.
   • → development/Data/preparation[Data preparation]
   • Use prepared data to create the → development/Data/mining/model[models]
   • Evaluate the → development/Data/mining/model[models]
   • Finally, use the (best) model to score new data
